            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>31 October 1853</date>
            </p>
            <p>My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours of the <date>27th</date> I recd with the<lb/>
                <date>Oct</date> Occidents which came in tolerable good season</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose herein the Amount of my collections<lb/> up to this date,
                the moment the business season<lb/> closes I will endeavor to collect mine and
                send<lb/> same to you as I have no doubt that it will be<lb/> useful whilst so much
                engaged in publications</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The most favorable season for the<lb/> disposal of your prayer Books
                would be during<lb/> the Autumn Holidays, when there is usually an<lb/> anxiety to
                have Books-possibly they may be<lb/> inquired for again in <date>Passover</date> but
                not to such<lb/> an extent as for <date>Atonement</date>. It would be well<lb/>
                could your edition be made as portable &amp; small<lb/> as the English. It seems
                very unfortunate<lb/> that you should not have complied with <persName>Mr<lb/> De
                    Sola's</persName> request—to return to him his manuscript<lb/> unless published
                in <date>October</date> Number. He states<lb/> his confidence of having written his
                wishes quite</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>distinctly. I must admit his right to the return of<lb/> the document—if you found
                yourself unable to insert<lb/> it as directed. However as you will refrain from<lb/>
                adding any remarks of your own should you insert<lb/> his answer in the
                    <date>Novr.</date> Occident, now on the way to us<lb/> if is useless discussing
                the matter any further—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You would not review <persName>Mr Raphael</persName> book
                because<lb/> you deemed it unworthy of a favorable notice, but<lb/> you had no such
                hesitation as regards <persName>Mr Desolas</persName> you admit In this I can only
                see an absence of all anxiety to “satisfy people” As you have often derived
                    <del>in</del> having<lb/> been a Candidate for reelection by your late
                congregation<lb/> I cannot understand how you <sic>shuld</sic> consider enemies<lb/>
                those who vote for avowed candidates or why you should exhibit<lb/> such enmity
                towards those who have been Candidates.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Morais</persName> seems to <add>?</add> himself to give
                satisfaction to all and to be at enmity with none—these<lb/> qualities, no doubt,
                secured him the support of <persName>Mr Jratz<add>?</add></persName><lb/> and will
                possibly obtain for him a life election.<lb/> You must admit that it is but natural
                for a<lb/> congregation to retain the services of a Minister who<lb/> is popular
                with all. If <persName>Mr Desola</persName> were at enmity<lb/> with three members
                of his congregation they vote<lb/> could keep him in, I would not give it to
                him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our weather has been delightful with little cold.</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>3</p>
            <p>I suppose you will not travel northward this<lb/> season. <persName>Mr
                    Joseph</persName> &amp; family are quite family<add>?</add><lb/> she desires her
                best regards to you. My mother is<lb/> as well as could be expected</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If I can get suitable Bills I will endure<lb/> here in twenty one
                dollar of which, the following<lb/> are to be acknowledged w next
                <sic>oxident</sic><lb/> say <add>?</add>. <persName>Desola</persName> &amp;
                    <persName>Mr Joseph</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I expect to be in <placeName>New York</placeName> for one day<lb/>
                this week. Believe me Ever</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yrs Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">J Joseph</persName>
            </p>
